{"rappelLongestMeters":30.48,"permit":"No","timeRating":"III","url":"https:\/\/ropewiki.com\/Ledbetter_Creek","name":"Ledbetter Creek","id":73354,"vehicle":"Passenger","rappelCountMin":6,"description":"<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><p>This is a TRUE SLOT CANYON in the southeast.  While it is not as serious as most of the canyons out west, this is not a place for beginners.  You should not enter this canyon until you understand how to inspect and replace anchors, until you are competent at rappelling, and it is preferred that you know how to build a contingency anchor and that you know how to ghost anchors.  If you get hurt or stuck in this canyon, SAR will have a hard time getting you out. \n<\/p><p>While this canyon is getting more and more traffic, it is still not run extremely often.  You should be prepared to replace anchors (bring ~30 ft webbing for sure and preferably a couple of quick links).  It is preferred to use black webbing as photographers will hike up from the bottom to photograph the falls, and would probably get annoyed if there is a bright orange piece of webbing at the top of the falls.  Since this is a location that people have historically bushwhacked up to, it is good practice to ghost all the rappels that are not ghosted.  However, this is absolutely not the place to learn how to do that.  If you need to leave anchors behind, please use black webbing.  Keep this in mind, as if you need anchors placed, you should not come expecting them to be here (plan to bring webbing and quick links)\n<\/p><p>Things you should know before entering this canyon: \n<\/p>\n<ul><li>How to rappel single strand<\/li>\n<li>How to give a fireman's belay<\/li>\n<li>How to communicate with a whistle or hand signals (communicating over 1000 ft with a waterfall between you can be challenging with your voice)<\/li>\n<li>How to set a biner block, and preferably how to set a contingency anchor (figure 8 block, macrame, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>How to add or remove friction from your rappel device mid rappel (Canyoneering specific devices such as the Imlay Critr, Sterling ATC, or BG Sqwurel make this exceptionally easy compared to climbing and caving devices)<\/li>\n<li>How determine if an anchor is good enough (tree diameter, root structure, location compared to rappel, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>How to build an anchor (how to tie a water knot, how to keep webbing at desired height, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>How to self-rescue (how to lower a stuck rappeler, how to ascend back up a rope, how to lower a hurt member of the party, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>Simple first aid - It is a pretty easy place for someone to get hurt, the rock is slick, the creek walk would be an easy place for someone to break an ankle, almost everyone I have been with has fallen at some point or another during the trips, and you do not have service to call for help so it is best to be able to do simple first aid to be able to get someone who is hurt back to the car.<\/li><\/ul>\n<meta property=\"mw:PageProp\/toc\" \/>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Approach\">Approach<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Hike up the Bartram Trail.  You gain just over 1,000 feet in 1.5 miles.  Once the trail meets up with the creek, you can put on your wetsuit (if wearing one).  Then you will turn and follow the stream for 0.5 miles until you see the slot section.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Descent\">Descent<\/h2><\/div>\n<p><b>Before the Falls<\/b>\n<\/p>\n<ul><li>S1: 8 ft<\/li><\/ul>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r1062633282\">@media all and (max-width:720px){.mw-parser-output .content .thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){display:flex;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;align-content:flex-start;flex-direction:column}}body.skin-vector .mw-parser-output div.thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){font-size:94%;text-align:center;overflow:hidden;min-width:100px}body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output div.thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){margin:0 auto;max-width:100%!important}<\/style> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p><b>Notch Falls<\/b>\n<\/p>\n<ul><li>R0: 10 ft off tree DCL (you can also downclimb this section pretty easily)<\/li><\/ul>\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<ul><li>R1: 20 ft off two bolts DCL<\/li><\/ul>\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<ul><li>R2: 50 ft off two bolts DCR (two stage rappel with a 6 foot swim between them)<\/li><\/ul>\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p><br \/>\n<b>Ledbetter Canyon Falls<\/b>\n<\/p>\n<ul><li>R3: 75 ft off tree DCL (Option 1: Straight down the gully not in water.  Option 2: go right and use boulder as a redirect and go in the water *recommended*)<\/li><\/ul>\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<ul><li>R4: 75 ft off two bolts DCR<\/li><\/ul>\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<ul><li>R5: 90 ft off tree DCL<\/li><\/ul>\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1062633282\"> \n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Exit\">Exit<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Fun downclimbs after rappel 5. Rocks are really slippery, so confidence and experience downclimbing and traversing a creek is a must. \n<\/p><p>Follow the creek ~0.75 miles until it goes under a bridge.  You car will be about 20 feet after the bridge.  You can also hop back on the Bartram trail about 0.25 miles sooner and take that back to the parking area.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Red_tape\">Red tape<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Beta_sites\">Beta sites<\/h2><\/div>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https:\/\/gaeaphotos.com\/rappelling-the-notch-a-true-nc-slot-canyon\/\">https:\/\/gaeaphotos.com\/rappelling-the-notch-a-true-nc-slot-canyon\/<\/a>\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Background\">Background<\/h2><\/div>\n\n\n<\/div>","shuttleSeconds":null,"rappelCountMax":6,"version":"9a676f1da8bb1dbad1f70e9744c707866e400a62db670ff7b3bf890fe36b52fc","waterRating":"C1","riskRating":null,"latitude":35.2921,"technicalRating":3,"longitude":-83.6797,"months":["Dec","Jan","Feb","Mar","Apr","May","Jun","Jul","Aug","Sep","Oct","Nov"],"geojson":{"type":"FeatureCollection","features":[{"properties":{"name":"R4 - 80 ft - Bolts RDC"},"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-83.67763879930972,35.28817307452472,0]]},"type":"Feature"},{"properties":{"name":"R5 - 100 ft - Tree LDC "},"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-83.67748,35.28798,0]],"type":"Point"},"type":"Feature"},{"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-83.67775,35.2883,0]]},"type":"Feature","properties":{"name":"R3 - 75 ft - Tree LDC"}},{"type":"Feature","geometry":{"coordinates":[[-83.67705,35.28594,0]],"type":"Point"},"properties":{"name":"Cool Cave Downclimb - DCL"}},{"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-83.67847,35.28895,0]],"type":"Point"},"properties":{"name":"R1 - 20 ft - Bolts LDC"},"type":"Feature"},{"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-83.6786,35.28933,0]]},"type":"Feature","properties":{"name":"S1 - 10 ft"}},{"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-83.67854,35.28903,0]]},"properties":{"name":"R0 - 10ft - Tree LDC"},"type":"Feature"},{"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-83.67845,35.28893,0]]},"type":"Feature","properties":{"name":"R2 - 50 ft - Bolts - RDC"}},{"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-83.67404222488405,35.28251660360971,0]],"type":"Point"},"type":"Feature","properties":{"name":"Parking"}},{"type":"Feature","geometry":{"coordinates":[[-83.6797419190407,35.29209739572262,0]],"type":"Point"},"properties":{"name":"Drop-In"}},{"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-83.6740529537201,35.28250565598673,0],[-83.67418974637987,35.28258885788437,0],[-83.67409050464632,35.282718039608675,